HEADWORD: Meninges
<hw>Me*nin"ges</hw> <pr>(m⟦esl⟧*n⟦icr⟧n"j⟦emac⟧z)</pr>, <pos>n.
pl.</pos>; <sing>sing. <singw>Meninx</singw>
<pr>(m⟦esl⟧*n⟦icr⟧⟦nsm⟧ks")</pr></sing>. <ety>[NL., fr. Gr.
<grk>mh^nigx</grk>, <grk>mh^niggos</grk>, a membrane.]</ety>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>The three membranes that envelop the brain and
spinal cord; the pia mater, dura mater, and arachnoid
membrane.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Meningitis</ent>⟦br⟧
